      <scopecontent id="aspace_cc0863f9f332f254d397e1a0ee58af35">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The diary documents a young Irish couple's life in New Haven with observations on events and changes at Yale University during the late 1960s, including topics such as acting companies and theaters, American writers, the civil rights movement, and the Vietnam War.  The collection also includes an epilogue written by the Murrays in 2016, personal correspondence with family and a former professor after their time in New Haven, and newspaper clippings documenting events at Yale University.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_97e4fe834f8471b018b51e86f8de9a06">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Gift of Christopher and Kathleen Murray, 2018.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <bioghist id="aspace_0c09ce3035ea3b52ccab0943ae939fe0">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Christopher Murray was a graduate student in the Department of Theatre History, and Kathleen Murray was an employee of Yale University Press, circa 1965-1970. They moved to New Haven from Cobh, Ireland in 1965 after Christopher was accepted into the PhD program in History of Theatre at Yale University. They returned to Ireland in 1970.</p>  
      </bioghist>
